[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Reference implementations:** The following AWS sample resources demonstrate the patterns used in this recipe:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m >
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > - [`amazon-sagemaker-examples`](https://github.com/aws/amazon-sagemaker-examples): Official SageMaker examples including custom inference container patterns and probabilistic model deployment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > - [AWS Step Functions Workflow Studio](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/step-functions/latest/dg/workflow-studio.html): For visually composing the forecast pipeline including Distributed Map fan-out
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > - [AWS Glue Studio](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/glue/latest/dg/edit-jobs-chapter.html): For authoring the harmonization ETL jobs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m <!-- TODO (TechWriter): N1. Verify all reference implementation links are still live during the pre-publication audit. -->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 1: Ingest and harmonize multi-source surveillance feeds.** The pipeline starts by bringing every surveillance signal into a common analytic frame: common geographies (HHS regions, state, county, sentinel sites), common time grids (epi-week is the standard for respiratory virus work), and common units (counts per population, normalized concentrations for wastewater, share-of-visits for syndromic). The harmonization is far from trivial. ED syndromic data uses one geography schema, lab data uses another, wastewater uses a third tied to sewer-shed boundaries. Time alignment is non-obvious because epi-week starts on Sunday, calendar week on Monday, fiscal week on something else, and lab reports use receipt date while syndromic uses encounter date. Unit conversion has to handle population denominators that themselves are estimates with uncertainty. The harmonization layer is the single most underestimated component of every epidemic forecasting system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION harmonize_surveillance_feed(feed_specification, raw_data_partition, geography_registry, population_registry):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // The feed_specification is a versioned config that describes a single source:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   feed_id:                    "state-lab-respiratory-pcr"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   source_geography:           "lab_zip"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   source_time:                "specimen_collected_date"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   target_geography:           "county_fips"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   target_time_unit:           "epi_week"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   value_field:                "positive_count"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   denominator_field:          "tests_total"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   metric_kind:                "positivity_rate"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   reporting_lag_distribution: { p50: 4, p90: 11 }   // days
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     geography_map = geography_registry.lookup(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         from_schema = feed_specification.source_geography,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         to_schema   = feed_specification.target_geography
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     harmonized_rows = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR raw_row IN raw_data_partition:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Geography mapping. A lab ZIP may map to multiple counties (proportional);
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // the geography registry handles the proportional allocation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_geo_allocations = geography_map.allocate(raw_row.source_geography_value)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Time alignment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_time = compute_epi_week(raw_row[feed_specification.source_time])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Compute the metric value for this feed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF feed_specification.metric_kind == "positivity_rate":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             value = raw_row[feed_specification.value_field] / max(raw_row[feed_specification.denominator_field], 1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ELIF feed_specification.metric_kind == "rate_per_100k":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             population = population_registry.lookup(raw_row.source_geography_value, target_time.year)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             value = (raw_row[feed_specification.value_field] / population) * 100000
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ELIF feed_specification.metric_kind == "concentration_normalized":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             value = normalize_concentration(raw_row, feed_specification.normalization_config)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ELSE:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             value = raw_row[feed_specification.value_field]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR (target_geography_value, allocation_share) IN target_geo_allocations:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             harmonized_rows.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 feed_id:               feed_specification.feed_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 target_geography:      target_geography_value,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 target_time:           target_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 value:                 value * allocation_share,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 denominator_value:     raw_row.get(feed_specification.denominator_field) * allocation_share,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 source_record_count:   1 * allocation_share,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ingested_at_ts:        now(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 expected_revision:     should_expect_revision(target_time, feed_specification.reporting_lag_distribution),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 feed_specification_version: feed_specification.version
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write harmonized_rows to S3 harmonized/{feed_id}/{epi_year}/{epi_week}/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN harmonized_rows
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 2: Nowcast the current epidemiological state.** Every surveillance signal lags reality. Lab confirmations lag exposure by approximately a week through case incubation, presentation, testing, and reporting; the lag varies by signal and changes over time. A naive forecasting approach treats the most recent reported values as ground truth, which biases forecasts by anchoring them to a state-of-the-world that already happened. Nowcasting estimates the unobserved current epidemiological state given the lagged observations and the known reporting-delay distribution. The nowcast output is the input to the forecasting layer; its uncertainty propagates forward.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION nowcast_current_state(harmonized_signals, nowcast_config, reporting_delay_priors):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // nowcast_config specifies which signals to fuse and at what resolution:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   target_geographies:     ["county_fips"] or ["state_fips"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   target_metrics:         ["incidence_per_100k", "hospitalization_per_100k"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   nowcast_horizon:        4   // weeks back to estimate (because all data is lagged)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   model_family:           "bayesian_state_space"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   signal_weights:         { wastewater: 0.4, ed_syndromic: 0.3, lab_confirmed: 0.3 }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   reporting_delay_pmf:    per-signal probability mass functions of report lag
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Pull harmonized signals at the target resolution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     signal_panel = build_signal_panel(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         signals     = harmonized_signals,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         geographies = nowcast_config.target_geographies,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         time_window_weeks = nowcast_config.nowcast_horizon + 12
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Reverse the reporting-delay convolution. Each observed weekly count is the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // sum of contributions from cases occurring in earlier weeks, with the lag
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // distribution determining how much of each earlier week contributes. The
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // nowcast is the inverse: estimate the underlying weekly cases given the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // observed reports and the known lag distribution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     nowcast_state = fit_state_space_nowcast(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         signal_panel    = signal_panel,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         delay_priors    = reporting_delay_priors,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         config          = nowcast_config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // nowcast_state contains posterior median + credible intervals for each
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // (geography, time) cell over the nowcast_horizon.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Joint nowcast across signals (wastewater confirms the lab signal, both
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // confirm or contradict the syndromic). The joint posterior is tighter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // than any individual signal but only when signals agree. Disagreement
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // shows up as wider posterior uncertainty rather than as a wrong central
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // estimate.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     fused_nowcast = fuse_signals(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         nowcast_state    = nowcast_state,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         signal_weights   = nowcast_config.signal_weights
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write fused_nowcast to S3 nowcasts/{run_id}/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN fused_nowcast
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 3: Run the per-model forecast layer.** Each model family runs in parallel on the nowcast-conditioned input. Compartmental models (SEIR variants with the relevant stratifications) use the nowcast as the initial condition and project forward under specified parameter posteriors. Statistical models (ARIMA, gradient-boosted trees on lagged features, Prophet, neural network families) use the harmonized panel directly. Scenario models layer mitigation effects on top of the compartmental projections. The fan-out here is the workhorse of the pipeline; SageMaker Distributed Map runs each model on its own container with its own dependencies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION run_model_forecast(model_specification, fused_nowcast, harmonized_panel, forecast_horizon_weeks):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // model_specification example for a SEIR variant:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   model_id:               "seir-age-stratified-v3"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   model_family:           "compartmental"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   container_image:        "epi-models/seir-pymc:v3.2"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   stratifications:        ["age_band_5"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   parameters_prior:       { R0_mean: 1.5, R0_sd: 0.4, generation_time_days: 5.0, ... }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   forecast_horizon_weeks: 8
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   scenario:               null   // or { mitigation_id, contact_reduction_share }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compose model inputs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model_inputs = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         initial_state:         fused_nowcast.most_recent_state,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         initial_uncertainty:   fused_nowcast.most_recent_uncertainty,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         historical_signals:    harmonized_panel,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         forecast_horizon:      forecast_horizon_weeks,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         scenario_assumptions:  model_specification.scenario
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Invoke the model. For a Bayesian compartmental model, this is a sampling
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // step that produces posterior samples of forecast trajectories. For a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // statistical model, this is a quantile-regression or Monte-Carlo prediction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // call. Either way the output is a set of probabilistic forecasts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model_forecast = invoke_sagemaker_endpoint(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         endpoint_name = model_specification.endpoint,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         payload       = model_inputs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // model_forecast contains:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   - per-week probabilistic forecasts (quantiles or full posterior samples)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   - per-week credible intervals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   - assumed parameter posterior (for compartmental and Bayesian families)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     artifact = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model_id:                 model_specification.model_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         run_id:                   current_pipeline_run_id(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         nowcast_id:               fused_nowcast.id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         forecast_trajectories:    model_forecast.trajectories,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         forecast_quantiles:       model_forecast.quantiles,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         parameter_posterior:      model_forecast.parameter_posterior,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         scenario_assumptions:     model_specification.scenario,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         generated_at_ts:          now()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write artifact to S3 per-model-forecasts/{run_id}/{model_id}/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN artifact
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 4: Combine into an ensemble.** The empirical lesson from the FluSight and COVID-19 Forecast Hub work is that ensembles outperform individual models. The combination weighting can be inverse-variance, calibration-aware (weighted by past Weighted Interval Score), or simple equal-weighted as a robust default. The ensemble also reconciles disagreement between models: a tight ensemble means the models agree, a wide ensemble means there is real uncertainty across modeling approaches that the headline forecast must reflect.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION combine_ensemble(per_model_forecasts, ensemble_config, calibration_history):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // ensemble_config example:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   combination_method:      "wis_weighted"   // or "equal_weighted", "inverse_variance"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   weight_lookback_weeks:   12               // for WIS-weighted
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   minimum_models_required: 3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     //   discard_models_with_calibration_failure_within_weeks: 4
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compute per-model weights based on recent calibration performance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF ensemble_config.combination_method == "wis_weighted":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         weights = compute_wis_weights(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             forecasts          = per_model_forecasts,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             calibration_history = calibration_history,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             lookback_weeks     = ensemble_config.weight_lookback_weeks
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ELIF ensemble_config.combination_method == "equal_weighted":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         weights = equal_weights(per_model_forecasts)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ELIF ensemble_config.combination_method == "inverse_variance":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         weights = inverse_variance_weights(per_model_forecasts)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Discard models with recent calibration failures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     eligible_models = filter_eligible(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         per_model_forecasts,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         calibration_history,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ensemble_config.discard_models_with_calibration_failure_within_weeks
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF count(eligible_models) < ensemble_config.minimum_models_required:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RAISE alert "insufficient_models_for_ensemble"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Combine quantile-by-quantile. The Vincentized quantile combination is
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // the standard for probabilistic forecast hubs; it averages the quantile
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // values rather than averaging across distributions, which preserves
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // the ensemble's calibration properties.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ensemble_forecast = vincentized_combination(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         per_model_forecasts = eligible_models,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         weights             = weights,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         quantile_grid       = standard_quantile_grid()  // 0.025, 0.05, 0.1, ..., 0.95, 0.975
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     artifact = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         run_id:                   current_pipeline_run_id(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ensemble_method:          ensemble_config.combination_method,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         per_model_weights:        weights,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         eligible_models:          [m.model_id for m in eligible_models],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ensemble_quantiles:       ensemble_forecast.quantiles,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ensemble_trajectories:    ensemble_forecast.trajectories,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         generated_at_ts:          now()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write artifact to S3 ensemble-forecasts/{run_id}/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN artifact
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 5: Validate calibration and surface the forecast.** Every forecast cycle, the pipeline evaluates the calibration of forecasts made N weeks ago against newly observed outcomes for those weeks. The metrics flow into a calibration tracker that alarms on drift. The calibrated forecasts are surfaced to operational systems (DynamoDB for low-latency consumption, Aurora for analytic and federal-publishing flows) and to dashboards (QuickSight for internal, CloudFront-fronted static for public).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION validate_and_surface(ensemble_forecast, observed_outcomes_for_past_horizons, run_metadata):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compute calibration metrics for forecasts made at past time points whose
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // forecast windows have now elapsed and have observed outcomes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     calibration_results = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR (past_run_id, past_forecast) IN past_forecasts_with_observable_outcomes():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         observed = lookup_observed_outcomes(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             geographies = past_forecast.geographies,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             time_range  = past_forecast.forecast_time_range
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         result = compute_calibration_metrics(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             forecast = past_forecast,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             observed = observed,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             metrics  = ["coverage_50", "coverage_80", "coverage_95", "wis", "crps"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         calibration_results.append(result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Aggregate calibration. Persist for the calibration tracker.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     aggregate_calibration = aggregate_metrics(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         calibration_results,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         by = ["geography", "horizon_weeks", "target"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write aggregate_calibration to Aurora calibration_history table
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Alarm on drift.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     drift_alarms = detect_calibration_drift(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         current   = aggregate_calibration,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline  = lookback_baseline_calibration(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         thresholds = drift_alarm_config()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF len(drift_alarms) > 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         publish_to_sns(drift_alarms)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Surface the new forecast to the operational store.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     operational_summaries = build_operational_summaries(ensemble_forecast)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR summary IN operational_summaries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         write summary to DynamoDB forecast-serving with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             partition_key = summary.geography
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             sort_key      = summary.target + "#" + summary.horizon
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Surface to the analytic registry.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write ensemble_forecast.full_artifacts to Aurora forecast_registry
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Refresh dashboards.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     trigger_quicksight_refresh()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     render_public_dashboard_assets()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         run_id:               run_metadata.run_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         operational_count:    len(operational_summaries),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         calibration_alarms:   drift_alarms,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         published_at_ts:      now()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Curious how this looks in Python?** The pseudocode above covers the concepts. If you'd like to see sample Python code that demonstrates these patterns using boto3, PyMC for the Bayesian compartmental layer, statsmodels for the statistical ensemble member, and Prophet for an additional baseline, check out the [Python Example](chapter12.09-python-example). It walks through each step with inline comments and notes on what you'd need to change for a real deployment.
