[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [CDC Center for Forecasting and Outbreak Analytics](https://www.cdc.gov/forecast-outbreak-analytics/index.html): The CFA program coordinates infectious-disease forecasting across pathogens and partners
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Reich Lab forecast tools and ensemble methods](https://reichlab.io/): Influential academic group whose ensemble methods underpin many production hubs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [CMU Delphi Group](https://delphi.cmu.edu/): Producers of multiple data sources and forecasting models, including the COVIDcast indicator API
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [PyMC](https://www.pymc.io/) and [Stan](https://mc-stan.org/): Bayesian modeling frameworks suitable for compartmental and hierarchical forecasting models
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Prophet](https://facebook.github.io/prophet/): Statistical forecasting framework widely used as a baseline ensemble member
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [`epyestim`](https://github.com/lo-hfk/epyestim) and [EpiNow2](https://github.com/epiforecasts/EpiNow2): R packages for effective reproduction number estimation and short-term epidemic forecasting
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Weighted Interval Score (Bracher et al. 2021)](https://journals.plos.org/ploscompbiol/article?id=10.1371/journal.pcbi.1008618): The standard probabilistic scoring rule used by the COVID-19 Forecast Hub and FluSight
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [POLYMOD contact study](https://journals.plos.org/plosmedicine/article?id=10.1371/journal.pmed.0050074): The widely-used age-stratified contact matrix that underpins many compartmental models
